# Next.js rendering (Cafing website)

## UI / theming (MUI)

- Use **Material UI** components; theme lives in `src/theme/` (see `website/docs/THEMING.md`).
- **Colors** — only in `src/theme/colors.ts`; components import `colors` from `@/theme/colors`. Never use hex/rgba literals in UI code.
- **Light theme** — matches light image-editor (jade + copper on warm neutrals).
- Shared layout: `PageContainer`, `PageHeader` from `@/components/layout/`.
- `ThemeRegistry` wraps the app — do not add a second `ThemeProvider`.

## Default: Server Components

- Pages under `src/app/` are **Server Components** unless they need browser-only behavior.
- Fetch data with `apiServer` from `@/lib/api-server` (uses `API_URL` on the server).
- Use `export const metadata` or `generateMetadata` on SEO routes.

## SEO / public routes (SSR required)

| Route | Rendering |
|-------|-----------|
| `/` | Server + `metadata` |
| `/studio` | Server + `generateMetadata` (template picker home) |
| `/studio/pricing` | Server + `metadata` |

## Private / interactive routes (client page OK)

| Route | Rendering |
|-------|-----------|
| `/studio/projects` | `'use client'` page |
| `/studio/account` | `'use client'` page |
| `/studio/cart` | `'use client'` page |

Use `apiClient` from `@/lib/api-client` only in client pages.

## Client components (`src/components/client/`)

Add `'use client'` only for:

- Event handlers (`onClick`, `onSubmit`, `useState`, `useEffect`)
- Examples: `SearchForm`, `CreateProjectButton`, `ActiveSidebar` (pathname for nav)

Do **not** mark presentational UI as client if it can be a link:

```tsx
// ✅ Server — crawlers and SSR see real hrefs
<a href={getEditorUrl({ templateId: t.id })} className="template-card">...</a>

// ❌ Avoid — full page client fetch for public catalog
'use client';
useEffect(() => { api.getTemplates() }, []);
```

## Editor redirects

- Server-safe: `getEditorUrl()` from `@/lib/editor`
- Client-only navigation after mutations: `openEditor()` from `@/lib/editor-client`

## API

| Module | Use in |
|--------|--------|
| `api-server.ts` | Server Components, `generateMetadata` |
| `api-client.ts` | `'use client'` pages only |

Server fetch must use absolute `API_URL` (e.g. `http://localhost:3001`), not relative `/api`.
